"" means, with respect to Limited Recourse Indebtedness, reasonable and customary exceptions for fraud, willful misrepresentation, misapplication of funds (including misappropriation of security deposits and failure to apply rents to operating expenses or debt service), indemnities relating to environmental matters and waste of property constituting security for such Limited Recourse Indebtedness, post-default interest, attorney's fees and other costs of collection to the extent not covered by the value of the property constituting security for such Limited Recourse Indebtedness and other similar exceptions to nonrecourse liability.
