Section 2.2
(a) Except as provided in of this Section, during such periods as such Loan is a Daily Reset LIBOR Rate Loan, a rate per annum equal to the lesser of (i) the sum of the Daily Reset LIBOR Rate in effect from time to time plus the Applicable Margin and (ii) the Highest Lawful Rate, payable monthly in arrears on the first day of each month commencing January 1, 2010, and on the Maturity Date, which interest may, at the discretion of the Agent, be paid by an Agent initiated Advance pursuant to or by a debit to a deposit account at U.S. Bank initiated by the Agent per any preauthorization provided by Borrower to the Agent, without prior demand by the Agent.
