(c) Borrower shall have the right, upon at least five Business Days' written notice to the Lenders, to terminate the Line of Credit A Loan Commitments, (i) in whole (subject to the last sentence of this ) or (ii) in part, in a minimum amount of $5,000,000 and an integral multiple of $1,000,000, but not to an amount less than $160,000,000. Provided, however, that any such termination shall be accompanied, (i) in the case of a termination in whole, by payment of the Line of Credit A Loan Liabilities in full and the return or cash coverage of any Letter then outstanding, or (ii) in the case of a partial termination, payment of the Line of Credit A Loan Liabilities to the extent necessary to cause the Available Amount A to be not less than zero. Any partial reduction of the Line of Credit A Loan Commitments pursuant to this shall result in a reduction pro-rata of the Line of Credit A Loan Commitments of each of the Lenders. Borrower shall have the right, upon at least five Business Days' written notice to the Lenders, to terminate the Line of Credit C Loan Commitments, (i) in whole, or (ii) in part, in a minimum amount of $5,000,000 and an integral multiple of $1,000,000, but not to an amount less than $160,000,000. Provided, however, that any such termination shall be accompanied, (i) in the case of a termination in whole, by payment of the Line of Credit C Loan Liabilities in full, or (ii) in the case of a partial termination, payment of the Line of Credit C Loan Liabilities to the extent necessary to cause the Available Amount C to be not less than zero. Any partial reduction of the Line of Credit C Loan Commitments pursuant to this shall result in a reduction pro-rata of the Line of Credit C Loan Commitments of each of the Lenders. In the event Borrower elects to terminate the Line of Credit A Loan Commitments in whole as set forth in this , then Borrower shall also terminate the Line of Credit C Loan Commitments in whole as set forth in this .
