Section 2.4
Borrower and its consolidated subsidiaries shall maintain proper books of record and account in accordance with GAAP consistently applied in which true, full and correct entries will be made of all their respective dealings and business affairs. If any changes in accounting principles are hereafter required or permitted by GAAP and are adopted by Borrower and its consolidated subsidiaries with the concurrence of its independent certified public accountants and such changes in GAAP result in a change in the method of calculation or the interpretation of any of the financial covenants, standards or terms found in or any other provision of this Agreement, Borrower and the Required Lenders agree to amend any such affected terms and provisions so as to reflect such changes in GAAP with the result that the criteria for evaluating Borrower's financial condition shall be the same after such changes in GAAP as if such changes in GAAP had not been made.
